egyptian 1986 crude oil output down on 1985 non-opec egypt produc 40.3 mln tonn ( about 295 mln barrel ) of crude in 1986 against 44.3 mln tonn ( about 323 mln barrel ) in 1985 , accord to offici figur relea today by the egyptian gener petroleum corp. ( egpc ) . offici say egypt can produc up to one mln bpd per day , but product wa cut when world price plung last year . in an attempt to help opec stabil the world market , egypt cut it 1987 product target of 940,000 bpd to it current output of 870,000 bpd . egypt , which export a third of it output , current sell it top suez and ra bahar blend for 17.25 dlr a barrel .